 convergence speed, test accuracy (>6% improvement over Adam and QHAdam), and resilience to dataset shift compared to existing methods. Ablation studies confirm the individual contributions of the noise-aware quadratic solver and confidence masking. By unifying principles from certified robustness, physical noise modeling, and hyperparameter-free optimization, NAQL offers a scalable, interpretable, and plug-and-play training layer for quantum machine learning that advances the practical deployment of VQCs in real-world settings.",
